name: CJ B.
text: Great food, great prices, even greater staff. Always super kind and ready to help. Definitely on the top of my list as my favorite D'Angelo's

name: Michael Garbarino
text: Great sandwich, a little pricey for what it is, but clean prompt service...

name: Kevin Hoye
text: 17 minutes for a sandwich that was cold didnt need to be cooked. Asked for a Turkey with swiss pocket with nothing but Turkey and swiss. Got all the way home 20 minutes away and it was covered in mayonnaise. DISGUSTING THREW IT OUT. 8.00 â€¦More

name: Margie Roman
text: Great attention even though they got my order wrong. But staff was polite

name: Elizabeth Akeley
text: Dirty store, staff were nice especially the girl that brought my food out. Good food but not worth the price.

name: Jeffrey Walls
text: Super friendly service at this D'Angelo's

name: Jim Blades
text: The service was fine but the sandwich (steak and cheese) had hardly any steak in it! Mostly bread.

name: Claude Dotson
text: The manager was very rude and her name is Cathy

name: Robert Frechette
text: Way too expensive for crap food

name: The Gaming Turtle
text: They honestly suck. Worst restaurant in all of Massachusetts.
